We’re excited to host Detroit-based multidisciplinary artist and harpist Ahya Simone at #OtherWorlds on May 19th, 2023.

Ahya Simone (@ahyasimone) is an eclectically elusive siren and multidisciplinary artist from Detroit. As a harpist, composer, and filmmaker, she traverses the world of sound, moving image, and performance. She integrates R&B/soul, jazz, and experimental elements into her works and performances. These unique creations have allowed Ahya to collaborate with internationally renowned artists such as Brian Jackson, Saul Williams, Shigeto, Kelela, and Juliana Huxtable.

🗓️ Friday, May 19th
🕕 Doors open at 6:30PM
🌐 Location: @blackmarketnubian
📋 Register: bit.ly/otherworlds-ahya

We care deeply about making this event accessible to all members of our working-class BIPOC community, which is why we are offering sliding-scale tickets from $0-$30. As we anticipate a high level of interest in this event, we kindly ask that you choose your ticket tier with care and consideration for your financial situation.

HEY BERLIN ! Excited to be a part of this historic moment honoring Afro-German singer Marie Nejar in @klosterruine.berlin tomorrow at 5pm . Thankful to collaborate with @toxithegoat , @__julianebischoff and the Heinrich Boell Stiftung for this performance. This is a free event!

“With 3 Songs for Marie Nejar, James Gregory Atkinson investigates music as a space of memory. His work addresses the absence of Afro-German experience within established narratives. Marie Nejar, born in 1930 in Mühlheim an der Ruhr, began performing as a singer under the name Leila Negra at the beginning of the 1950s. Her life was shaped by the racist exclusions of Nazi Germany and its continuities into post-war Germany. Detroit harpist Ahya Simone will interpret songs by Nejar, following Atkinson’s invitation. The performance takes up an expanded conception of archives, in which places, bodies and oral as well as performative practices are understood as historical carriers.

Hey Berlin! Me and @toxithegoat at @klosterruine.berlin

A REVERIE FOR BRÈ

Dear friends far and wide,

My Beloved Sister Bré Rivera of over 11 years, visionary of the Black Trans Fund, and co-star of Femme Queen Chronicles  always lights up the world around her. This harp clip is but  a small representation of who she is.  She is a force and and woman of her own mind and spirit and creation. She touches the lives of many with her determination, kindness and generosity. And it is always a gift to witness her. 
Right now, she needs our support with her self-recovery journey towards claiming her birthright of healing, wellness, and joy. She has taken the first step, through her commitment and intention, by attending a wellness facility, and now she is depending on us to help with the cost of her 30-day stay there. The cost is $40,000. Let us champion Bré as a model for what’s possible when we proactively organize around our critical need for care and rehabilitation. Let us resist burn out, together. Tokyo food cam pt.1
The primordial is never recalled only re-experienced.

🧡Wow. Japan don’t owe me nothing! It was such a beautiful time to rest, retreat and to connect with my old and new friends abroad. Deciding to spend a month long birthday vacation was the greatest gift I could have ever given to myself. The gift of wanderlust and adventure. I’m so thankful for my loved ones who supported this trip to a place that I hold dear and allow me to rest and recharge my faith,mind and body.  It was a dream come true. I return with a  sense of possibility, of desire and the joy of feeling pleasure and hope and creativity. I return with clarity and grace. I returned to me. And made some new friends along the way. Sidereal Leo season is over but the celebration continues! Until my next solar year Japan! And Thank you all the people that I met. Y’all have made my year in a way y’all don’t even know! Stay tuned! I have some exciting news to announce soon!🧡

𝟑𝐡𝐝 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟑:🎻The Pleasure of Pain🎻
#AhyaSimone is performing #3hdFestival’s “The Pleasure of Pain” evening of music and theater at Berlin’s #HeimathafenNeukölln on November 2.

Tickets via 🔗 in bio.

A part of #CreamcakeBerlin’s 3hd: “Let Them Eat Cake” events program, the Detroit-based harpist, composer, and filmmaker, traverses the world of sound, moving image, and performance. Ever since she began singing in a church choir as a child, her passion for music has only grown since she was introduced to the harp as a teen.

Drawing inspiration from her favorite contemporary artists, Simone began to mix #RnB, #soul, #jazz, and experimental elements into her works and performances precipitated collaborations with renowned artists such as #BrianJackson, #SaulWilliams, #Shigeto, #Kelela, and #JulianaHuxtable, as well as membership in New York-based artist collective #PiqueProject.

Artwork by @claire_barrow

Für die erste Graveyard Shift der Spielzeit ist die multidisziplinäre Künstlerin @ahyasimone zu Gast. Simones Instrument der Wahl ist die Harfe, deren klassischen Referenzrahmen sie immer wieder mühelos erweitert durch Elemente des R&B, Soul und Jazz. Neben ihrer Arbeit als Solokünstlerin ist sie Teil des erweiterten Umfelds von Moved by the Motion, kollaboriert mit @kelela oder zeichnet sich für die Webserie @fqchronicles verantwortlich. Geeint ist diese künstlerische Vielfalt durch die stetige Reflexion von Fragen nach Schwarzer Identität, Ästhetik und Gemeinschaft.

Graveyard Shift ist eine Kooperation zwischen dem Schauspielhaus Zürich und @bad_bonn , kuratiert von Daniel Fontana und Mathis Neuhaus.

All that I have learned about love I’ve learned thru time. The only thing that differentiates the past from the future is heat. 
Otherwise, the past and future are one. 

Love requires the heat of desire 
Love requires air to sustain the fire 
Love requires movement to spread its allure
Love requires warm hearts that are ever so pure.

And I’m so grateful to share the warmth
of a heart so pure with @uncleeli . My Beloved Dreamer- the vision you possess saw me and I’m forever touched by your flame.
Thank you for these 5 earth years. That may seem like a long time but as a girl from Neptune it’s been a beautifully transformative blink of the eye. 🔱💙✨😭

To many more my Darling✨ 

✨Happy Anniversary✨

Wow. 
✨🧜🏽‍♀️Utrecht was a dream come true. Im still boiling over with joy from this weekend. To share the stage some of the most amazingly talented, experimental and magical artists worldwide. Endlessly thankful to all that attended, to @le_guess_who  and the amazing staff and of course thank you to  @thatboiakathatboi for curating me for this festival. I have cried multiple times in joy of discovering artists that I didn’t know I needed to know and even finally meeting some faves for the first time. My curiosity and sense possibility in art/music making is irrevocably changed. And then to arrive at the airport and was notified that I’m in the Dutch news, I ran to the nearest news stand!  This was the truly unexpected cherry on top. I’m so thankful. Until next time Netherlands! I have so much more highlights to share soon
💓✨💓
